What is a Function?
     A function is a block of code that performs a specific task when called.
     Similar to functions in programming languages like Python or C.


Basic Syntax
function functionName(parameters) visibility stateMutability returns(returnType) {
    // logic
}
Function Name :
           The name used to call the function
           Example: add, checkAge

Parameters (Input) :
            Values passed into the function
            function add(uint a, uint b)
            a and b are parameters

Visibility :
    Defines who can call the function
               public → anyone can call
               private → only inside the contract
               internal → inside contract + derived contracts
               external → only from outside

State Mutability :
        Defines how the function interacts with blockchain data:
          view → reads state, does not modify
          pure → does not read or modify state
          (none) → can modify state

Return Values :
       Specifies what the function returns:
       returns(uint)



















